description.text: Radian Per Minute (rad/min) is a unit in the category of Angular velocity. It is also known as radians per minute, radian/minute. Radian Per Minute (rad/min) has a dimension of aT-1 where $T$ is time. It can be converted to the corresponding standard SI unit rad/s by multiplying its value by a factor of 0.0166666666667.
